isting%2C%20and%20just%20don't%20break%20it.%20Don't%20run%20out%20of%20stock.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Eugene%20Khayman%2C%20cofounder%20of%20the%20exclusive%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-million-dollar-sellers-a-club-for-top-ecomm-entrepreneurs-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMillion%20Dollar%20Sellers%20club%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20started%20listing%20fitness%20and%20kitchen%20items%20on%20Amazon%20about%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20his%20product%20selection%20wasn't%20based%20on%20data%20or%20metrics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20just%20100%25%20feeling%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20wasn't%20much%20research%20as%20far%20as%20what%20had%20traffic%20because%20such%20tools%20and%20data%20weren't%20even%20available%20at%20that%20point%2C%20so%20it%20was%20very%20much%20like%20looking%20for%20a%20product%20and%20thinking%2C%20'Oh%2C%20that%20looks%20cool.%20Maybe%20I%20should%20try%20selling%20it.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202025%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-shop-live-selling-future-of-e-commerce-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eselling%20on%20Amazon%20is%20much%20more%20competitive%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20to%20survive%2C%20product%20selection%20is%20key.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20asked%20elite%20sellers%2C%20including%20Harrington%2C%20Khayman%2C%20and%20Alex%20Yale%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-make-money-online-according-to-successful-ecommerce-entrepreneur-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eruns%20two%20seven-figure%20Amazon%20brands%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20weigh%20in%20on%20the%20keys%20to%20selecting%20a%20winning%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221cc4e352-fcd0-4f45-9c91-527f553449ba%5C%22%3E1.%20Create%20something%20you%20can%20patent%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTry%20for%20some%20IP%20advantage%20if%20you%20can%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Yale%2C%20whose%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.flipitcap.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFlip-It!%20Cap%3C%2Fa%3E%20product%20is%20patent-protected.%20%26quot%3BI%20stay%20away%20from%20any%20Chinese-sourced%20products%20that%20don't%20have%20a%20patent%20or%20any%20kind%20of%20IP%20protection%2C%20because%20within%20two%20months%2C%20if%20you%20see%20success%20on%20a%20product%20that%20you%20import%20from%20China%2C%20they'll%20be%20selling%20it%20for%2020%25%20to%2030%25%20less%20on%20Amazon%20and%20competing%20with%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20explained%20that%20a%20major%20problem%20for%20e-commerce%20entrepreneurs%20in%202025%20is%20competing%20with%20Chinese%20sellers%20who%20can%20cut%20the%20middleman%20by%20manufacturing%20their%20own%20products%2C%20then%20selling%20directly%20on%20Amazon.%20One%20way%20to%20avoid%20the%20competition%20outright%20is%20to%20sell%20patented%20products%20that%20nobody%20can%20copy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20what%20Harrington%20does.%20A%20few%20years%20into%20selling%20interior%20cat%20doors%2C%20she%20decided%20to%20patent%20her%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22lisa%20harrington%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68bb1db2f9db348adc0aefca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHarrington%20has%20designed%20and%20patented%20multiple%20interior%20cat%20doors.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Lisa%20Harrington%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20gut%20told%20me%20that%20it%20was%20going%20to%20be%20a%20big%20deal%2C%20and%20I%20should%20really%20invest%20in%20intellectual%20property%2C%20so%20I%20found%20the%20best%20attorney%20I%20could%20and%20spent%20%2410%2C000%20on%20a%20patent%20application%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20She%20now%20has%2010%20patented%20products%2C%20and%20her%20brand%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpurrfectportal.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPurrfect%20Portal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20is%20the%20No.%201%20selling%20cat%20door%20on%20Amazon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20doesn't%20think%20her%20original%20product%20%E2%80%94%20dog%20harnesses%2C%20which%20profited%20enough%20in%20the%20early%202010s%20to%20fund%20Purrfect%20Portal%20%E2%80%94%20would%20survive%20today%20as%20an%20unpatented%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20wouldn't%20be%20able%20to%20make%20any%20money%20doing%20it.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20you're%20competing%20with%20brands%20that%20are%20the%20factory%20or%20have%20a%20lower%20cost%20of%20goods%2C%20and%20so%20it's%20really%20hard%20as%20an%20American%20brand%20to%20compete%20that%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarrington%20continued%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20to%20really%20succeed%20on%20Amazon%20today%2C%20you%20need%20to%20have%20a%20moat%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20moat%20is%20either%20something%20that%20is%20sourced%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20something%20that%20is%20very%20difficult%20to%20make%2C%20or%20intellectual%20property%2C%20like%20a%20utility%20patent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d2c5340e-cb1d-4a0b-ba70-3df180b6c1b8%5C%22%3E2.%20Calculate%20the%20TAM%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20TAM%2C%20or%20total%20addressable%20market%2C%20is%20the%20total%20revenue%20potential%20for%20your%20product%20if%20it%20were%20to%20capture%20the%20entire%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECalculating%20TAM%2C%20which%20you%20can%20do%20by%20multiplying%20the%20total%20number%20of%20potential%20customers%20by%20the%20average%20revenue%20per%20customer%2C%20will%20help%20you%20decide%20whether%20or%20not%20the%20market%20is%20worth%20going%20after.%20Is%20there%20enough%20demand%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20the%20first%20question%20Yale%20asks%20himself%20before%20launching%20any%20new%20products.%20If%20the%20answer%20is%2C%20%3Cem%3Eyes%2C%20the%20market%20is%20big%20enough%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehe%20starts%20to%20think%20about%20how%20he%20could%20create%20something%20distinguishing%20from%20existing%20competitors%3A%20%26quot%3BWhat%20can%20I%20do%20better%20or%20differently%20than%20what's%20out%20there%20today%2C%20so%20I%20can%20compel%20and%20convert%20customers%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20if%20you're%20looking%20to%20build%20a%20lasting%20brand%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20need%20to%20be%20in%20a%20market%20that%20has%20a%20TAM%20that's%20big%20enough%20for%20you%20to%20grow%2C%26quot%3B%20added%20Khayman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a0b43598-e947-497b-8b66-85072b7f6c47%5C%22%3E3.%20Create%20a%20product%20that%20solves%20a%20problem%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLaunch%20products%20that%20solve%20problems%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Yale%2C%20who%20has%20found%20success%20selling%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uncletodds.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeco-friendly%20cleaning%20products%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20as%20septic%20pods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20start%20a%20brand%20and%20you're%20chasing%20a%20fad%2C%20you%20might%20have%20a%20couple%20of%20great%20years%2C%20but%20over%20time%2C%20your%20sales%20are%20going%20to%20slide%20with%20the%20fad%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20If%20you%20want%20to%20build%20a%20brand%20that%20has%20staying%20power%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20do%20that%20by%20solving%20everyday%20problems%20with%20everyday%20consumers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22alex%20yale%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68bb1da1f9db348adc0aefc4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlex%20Yale%20is%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20cleaning%20brand%20Uncle%20Todd's%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Alex%20Yale%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EStart%20by%20thinking%20about%20your%20own%20life%20and%20the%20problems%2C%20big%20or%20small%2C%20that%20you%20face.%20That's%20how%20Harrington's%20cat%20door%20business%20came%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20a%20cat%20lady%20%E2%80%94%20I've%20always%20been%20a%20cat%20lady%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I%20really%20wanted%20an%20interior%20cat%20door.%20When%20I%20went%20online%2C%20there%20was%20only%20one%20option%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20And%20it%20wasn't%20what%20she%20was%20looking%20for%3A%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20the%20quintessential%2C%20'I%20can%20do%20this%20better.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22171e72e4-253e-45ca-8442-21fb5d6ef768%5C%22%3E4.%20Selling%20consumables%20is%20easier%20than%20selling%20one-time%20products%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYale%20recommends%20picking%20a%20product%20that%20people%20need%20to%20buy%20over%20and%20over%20again.%20All%20of%20his%20cleaning%20products%20are%20consumables%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%2C%20if%20his%20customers%20like%20the%20product%2C%20they'll%20likely%20be%20returning%20to%20buy%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSelling%20a%20one-time%20product%20that%20you%20can't%20get%20repeat%20purchases%20on%20is%20really%20difficult%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20That's%20because%20acquiring%20new%20customers%20is%20challenging%20and%20expensive.%20%26quot%3BBut%20my%20hope%20is%20that%20if%20somebody%20buys%20it%20once%2C%20then%20in%20six%20or%2012%20months%2C%20they'll%20come%20back%20and%20buy%20it%20again%2C%20and%20I%20won't%20have%20to%20keep%20acquiring%20that%20customer%20every%20single%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-online-sellers-can-pick-profitable-products-to-sell-on-amazon-2025-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1757155801000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68bb12a8f9db348adc0aed55%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-online-sellers-can-pick-profitable-products-to-sell-on-amazon-2025-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BTo%20really%20succeed%20on%20Amazon%20today%2C%20you%20need%20to%20have%20a%20moat%2C%26quot%3B%20says