20why%20Americans%20and%20America%20were%20left%20behind%2C%26quot%3B%20Desai%20said.%20%26quot%3BLook%20no%20further%20than%20lopsided%20'free'%20trade%20arrangements%20that%20let%20foreign%20cheating%20decimate%20our%20industrial%20base.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e8c73ecd-4d21-4442-ae17-23677831dd65%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'That's%20not%20the%20role%20for%20the%20United%20States%20government'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20deal%2C%20the%20US%20government%20is%20investing%20%248.9%20billion%20in%20Intel%20stock%2C%20funded%20primarily%20by%20grants%20that%20the%20company%20would%20have%20received%20under%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-joint-address-chips-act-horrible-bill-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECHIPS%20and%20Science%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%202022%20law%20signed%20by%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20aimed%20at%20spurring%20semiconductor%20manufacturing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20will%20make%20the%20US%20government%20the%20largest%20single%20investor%20in%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20deal%20came%20seemingly%20out%20of%20nowhere.%20Days%20earlier%2C%20Trump%20said%20Intel%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fintel-ceo-trump-demand-resign-stock-price-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ELip-Bu%20Tan%20should%20resign%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20calling%20him%20%26quot%3Bconflicted%26quot%3B%20over%20his%20connections%20to%20Chinese%20companies.%20Then%20led%20to%20a%20White%20House%20meeting%20between%20Tan%20and%20Trump%2C%20which%20resulted%20in%20the%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20and%20one%20of%20his%20top%20economic%20advisors%20have%20indicated%20that%20this%20could%20be%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-says-the-intel-deal-is-just-the-beginning-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efirst%20of%20many%20such%20deals%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20sure%20that%20at%20some%20point%20there'll%20be%20more%20transactions%2C%20if%20not%20in%20this%20industry%20then%20other%20industries%2C%26quot%3B%20Kevin%20Hassett%2C%20director%20of%20the%20National%20Economic%20Council%2C%20said%20in%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plan%20bears%20some%20resemblance%20to%20a%20years-old%20proposal%20from%20Sanders%20and%20Democratic%20Sen.%20Elizabeth%20Warren%20of%20Massachusetts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20duo%20offered%20an%20amendment%20to%20the%20CHIPS%20Act%20that%20would%20have%20required%20companies%20receiving%20funding%20via%20the%20bill%20to%20issue%20warrants%20or%20equity%20stakes%20to%20the%20US%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20amendment%20also%20had%20other%20conditions%2C%20including%20a%20ban%20on%20stock%20buybacks%20and%20required%20the%20company%20to%20remain%20neutral%20in%20union%20organizing%20efforts.%20It%20was%20ultimately%20not%20included%20in%20the%20final%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20glad%20the%20Trump%20administration%20is%20in%20agreement%20with%20the%20amendment%20I%20offered%20three%20years%20ago%20to%20the%20CHIPS%20Act%2C%26quot%3B%20Sanders%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BIf%20microchip%20companies%20make%20a%20profit%20from%20the%20generous%20grants%20they%20receive%20from%20the%20federal%20government%2C%20the%20taxpayers%20of%20America%20have%20a%20right%20to%20a%20reasonable%20return%20on%20that%20investment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESanders%20added%20that%20the%20Trump%20administration%20%26quot%3Bshould%20also%20make%20sure%20that%20these%20companies%20will%20not%20engage%20in%20illegal%20union%20busting%2C%20outsource%20American%20jobs%20overseas%20or%20buy%20back%20their%20own%20stock.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWarren%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20has%20been%20less%20willing%20to%20praise%20Trump's%20move.%20This%20week%2C%20she%20sent%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.banking.senate.gov%2Fimo%2Fmedia%2Fdoc%2Fletter_to_commerce_dept_re_intel-chips.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eletter%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Commerce%20Secretary%20Howard%20Lutnick%20excoriating%20the%20administration%20for%20not%20attaching%20more%20conditions%20to%20the%20money%20%E2%80%94%20and%20for%20dropping%20conditions%20that%20initially%20came%20with%20the%20CHIPS%20Act%20funding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20waived%20all%20of%20the%20requirements%20that%20would%20make%20the%20taxpayer%20investment%20in%20that%20company%20work%20for%20the%20American%20people%2C%20and%20effectively%20just%20became%20one%20more%20profit-maximizing%20investor%2C%26quot%3B%20Warren%20told%20BI%20on%20Thursday%2C%20referring%20to%20Trump.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20the%20role%20for%20the%20United%20States%20government.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20progressives%20have%20said%20they%20had%20little%20problem%20with%20the%20government%20taking%20a%20stake%20in%20a%20private%20company%2C%20but%20viewed%20Trump's%20move%20as%20incomplete.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20no%20problem%20with%20the%20American%20taxpayers%20being%20reluctant%20shareholders%20in%20Intel%2C%26quot%3B%20Democratic%20Rep.%20Ro%20Khanna%20of%20California%20said%20on%20NBC's%20%26quot%3BMeet%20the%20Press%26quot%3B%20on%20Sunday%2C%20though%20he%20said%20the%20company%20needed%20billions%20more%20in%20investment%20and%20that%20the%20government%20should%20use%20the%20agreement%20to%20push%20the%20company%20to%20sign%20a%20labor%20neutrality%20agreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDemocratic%20Rep.%20Mark%20Pocan%20of%20Wisconsin%20said%20that%20Trump%20needed%20a%20broader%20industrial%20policy%2C%20versus%20ad-hoc%20agreements%20with%20individual%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20just%20do%20ideas%20here%2C%20and%20ideas%20there%2C%20and%20expect%20it%20to%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20Pocan%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BEven%20if%20there's%20something%20good%20to%20an%20idea%2C%20without%20the%20other%20components%2C%20it%20doesn't%20have%20the%20effectiveness.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrumps-intel-deal-draws-praise-progressives-2025-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1757153221000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68b9c939f9db348adc0ad61b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrumps-intel-deal-draws-praise-progressives-2025-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BI%20am%20glad%20the%20Trump%20administration%20is%20in%20agreement%20with%20the%20amendment%20I%20offered%20three%20years%20ago%20to%20the%20CHIPS%20Act%2C%26quot%3B%20Sen.%20Bernie%20Sanders%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bmetzger%40insider.com%20(Bryan%20Metzger)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A86%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrumps-intel-deal-draws-praise-progressives-2025-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20deleted%20every%20app%20on%20my%20phone%20except%20for%20calls%20and%20texts.%20It%20changed%20how%20I%20thought%2C%20slept%2C%20and%20spoke%20to%20people.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227285%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22c%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68b75b06a17a8c5b4053e35d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3Ec%3Cp%3Ebymuratdeniz%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EI%20was%20struggling%20to%20concentrate%2C%20sleep%2C%20and%20connect%20with%20people%20because%20I%20was%20addicted%20to%20my%20phone.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%20decided%20to%20delete%20all%20my%20apps%2C%20including%20email%2C%20so%20that%20my%20phone%20would%20only%20receive%20calls%20and%20texts.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20drastic%20change%20helped%20me%20stay%20more%20present%20and%20clear-headed.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20past%20year%20has%20been%20all%20about%20getting%20rid%20of%20toxic%20traits%20and%20relationships.%20I%20ended%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flong-distance-relationship-success-started-with-14-hour-date-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eromantic%20relationships%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20drained%20me.%20I%20distanced%20myself%20from%20false%20friends.%20I%20walked%20away%20from%20professional%20situations%20that%20left%20me%20burned%20out%2C%20and%20I%20cut%20back%20on%20alcohol%20after%20realizing%20it%20had%20become%20more%20of%20a%20crutch%20than%20a%20celebration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20of%20those%20changes%20was%20deliberate.%20But%20there%20was%20one%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Ftoxic-relationship%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etoxic%20relationship%3C%2Fa%3E%20I%20hadn't%20acknowledged%20%E2%80%94%20one%20I%20carried%20in%20my%20pocket%20every%20single%20day.%20My%20cellphone.%20More%20specifically%2C%20the%20apps%20that%20turned%20it%20from%20a%20tool%20into%20something%20that%20dictated%20how%20I%20spent%20my%20time%2C%20how%20I%20communicated%2C%20and%20even%20how%20I%20thought.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20crept%20in%20quietly%3A%20the%20late-night%20scrolling%20sessions%2C%20the%20reflex%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-are-push-notifications%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Echeck%20notifications%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20conversations%2C%20the%20way%20I'd%20reach%20for%20my%20phone%20without%20thinking%20the%20moment%20I%20felt%20bored%20or%20anxious.%20It%20wasn't%20dramatic%20like%20a%20fight%20with%20a%20friend%20or%20a%20bad%20hangover%2C%20but%20it%20was%20just%20as%20corrosive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20finally%20admitted%20to%20myself%20that%20my%20phone%20might%20be%20my%20most%20toxic%20relationship%2C%20I%20knew%20I%20had%20to%20do%20something%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2200b6a2bd-2ae4-460c-8c68-477e7376f34e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20breaking%20point%3A%20anxiety%2C%20bad%20sleep%2C%20and%20constant%20noise%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trigger%20wasn't%20a%20single%20event%20but%20a%20buildup%20of%20small%20signals%20I%20couldn't%20ignore.%20My%20sleep%20was%20wrecked.%20I'd%20lie%20awake%20for%20hours%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-ban-doom-scrolling-rednote-instagram-facebook-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Escrolling%20TikTok%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20Instagram%2C%20checking%20X%20or%20LinkedIn%2C%20convincing%20myself%20that%20one%20more%20video%20or%20article%20would%20relax%20me.%20Instead%2C%20I'd%20wake%20up%20anxious%2C%20already%20behind%2C%20because%20my%20brain%20had%20been%20buzzing%20long%20before%20my%20alarm%20went%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20top%20of%20that%2C%20my%20mood%20was%20unpredictable.%20I%20felt%20more%20irritable%2C%20more%20distracted%2C%20and%20less%20capable%20of%20focusing.%20I'd%20be%20mid-conversation%20with%20someone%20and%20realize%20I%20hadn't%20processed%20a%20single%20thing%20they'd%20said%20because%20my%20brain%20was%20still%20spinning%20from%20something%20I'd%20read%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bd562aa5-dace-40a8-8254-bf45caf604e0%5C%22%3EI%20deleted%20all%20my%20apps%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20one%20Sunday%20night%2C%20I%20made%20a%20decision.%20I%20deleted%20everything%3A%20Instagram%2C%20TikTok%2C%20X%2C%20LinkedIn%2C%20Spotify%2C%20YouTube%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fgoogle-maps-timeline%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGoogle%20Maps%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20WhatsApp%2C%20and%20even%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20apps%20I%20left%20were%20the%20green%20phone%20icon%2C%20the%20blue%20text%20bubble%2C%20and%20the%20other%20factory%20ones%20that%20come%20with%20an%20iPhone.%20I%20wanted%20to%20know%20what%20my%20life%20would%20be%20like%20if%20my%20phone%20stopped%20being%20a%20smartphone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20know%20if%20the%20decision%20would%20last%20a%20week%2C%20a%20day%2C%20or%20even%20a%20few%20hours.%20And%20I%20knew%