0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gatesnotes.com%2Fbusiness-adventures%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGates%20wrote%20in%202014%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20to%20succeed%20in%20business%2C%20executives%20like%20Gates%20suggest%20you'll%20find%20valuable%20guidance%20in%20books.%20Gates%20has%20said%20he%20reads%20about%2050%20books%20a%20year%2C%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20which%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbill-gates-favorite-books-2014-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ememoirs%20and%20educational%20works%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20environmental%20science%2C%20public%20health%2C%20and%20finance.%20Buffett%2C%20too%2C%20is%20an%20avid%20reader%20who's%20recommended%20Benjamin%20Graham's%20%26quot%3BThe%20Intelligent%20Investor%2C%26quot%3B%20among%20other%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwarren-buffett-favorite-books-2016-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWall%20Street-favored%20instructionals%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20powerful%20people%20in%20business%20have%20also%20evangelized%20the%20benefits%20of%20reading%20to%20their%20staff%3A%20Jeff%20Bezos%20reportedly%20required%20his%20senior%20managers%20at%20Amazon%20to%20read%20nonfiction%20books%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeff-bezos-favorite-business-books-2013-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etime%20management%20and%20innovation%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20books%20most%20frequently%20recommended%20to%20aspiring%20business%20leaders%20tend%20to%20have%20one%20thing%20in%20common%3A%20they're%20nonfiction.%20Last%20year%2C%20when%20Business%20Insider%20compiled%20a%20list%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F25-books-jeff-bezos-elon-musk-bill-gates-loved-read-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E20%20books%20loved%20by%20powerful%20executives%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20only%20one%20was%20a%20novel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20some%20experts%20and%20book-loving%20CEOs%20say%20the%20dearth%20of%20fiction%20on%20many%20business%20leaders'%20bookshelves%20%E2%80%94%20and%20particularly%20on%20men's%20%E2%80%94%20is%20a%20missed%20opportunity%20for%20growth.%20Having%20leaders%20who%20actively%20engage%20their%20imaginations%2C%20they%20say%2C%20helps%20sharpen%20vital%20soft%20skills%20that%20can%20help%20a%20budding%20CEO%20take%20their%20career%20to%20the%20next%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20just%20a%20cultural%20issue%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Tess%20Pawlisch%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20a%20communications%20agency%20and%20an%20avid%20reader%20of%20both%20fiction%20and%20nonfiction.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20actually%20a%20leadership%20one.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2208ce83f8-94ba-494a-a634-54aa847d8400%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EImagining%20a%20better%20workplace%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20fiction%20by%20definition%20encompasses%20the%20world%20of%20made-up%20stories%2C%20the%20genre%20has%20more%20to%20offer%20than%20pure%20entertainment.%20Researchers%20have%20found%20that%20literary%20fiction%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F38089170%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimprove%20our%20people%20skills%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20making%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS019188691100451X%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeasier%20to%20empathize%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20read%20emotions%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F38602788%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadapt%20to%20social%20cues%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJoseph%20Badaracco%2C%20professor%20of%20Business%20Ethics%20at%20Harvard%20University%2C%20teaches%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hbs.edu%2Fcoursecatalog%2F1562.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eelective%20called%20%26quot%3BThe%20Moral%20Leader%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20tasks%20MBA%20students%20with%20reading%20and%20discussing%20works%20of%20fiction.%20Though%20his%20syllabus%20has%20gone%20through%20many%20iterations%20over%20the%20past%20two%20decades%2C%20he%20said%20one%20thing%20remains%20constant%3A%20Students%20emerge%20with%20%26quot%3Ba%20much%20more%20realistic%20sense%20of%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCumulatively%2C%20I%20think%20they%20do%20broaden%20and%20deepen%20your%20understanding%20of%20people%20and%20yourself%20and%20situations%2C%26quot%3B%20Badaracco%20said%20of%20the%20works%20of%20fiction%20he%20assigns%20in%20his%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20research%20labs%20and%20classroom%20walls%2C%20the%20benefits%20of%20reading%20fiction%20have%20seemingly%20been%20eclipsed%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconsumerism-capitalism-optimization-culture-live-medium-average-good-enough-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoptimization%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E.%20People%20don't%20want%20a%20laborious%20search%20for%20meaning%3B%20they%20want%20step-by-step%20instructions%20and%20immediate%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPawlisch%20said%20she%20hears%20the%20same%20titles%20suggested%20to%20aspiring%20entrepreneurs%20ad%20nauseum%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Flearning%2F48-laws-of-power-side-hustle-success%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERobert%20Greene's%20%26quot%3BThe%2048%20Laws%20of%20Power%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20Dale%20Carnegie's%20%26quot%3BHow%20to%20Win%20Friends%20and%20Influence%20People%2C%26quot%3B%20Stephen%20R.%20Covey's%20%26quot%3BThe%207%20Habits%20of%20Highly%20Effective%20People%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20James%20Clear's%20%26quot%3BAtomic%20Habits%2C%26quot%3B%20all%20of%20which%20are%20also%20sitting%20on%20her%20bookshelf.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20these%20kinds%20of%20books%20push%20readers%20to%20refine%20their%20own%20routines%2C%20skills%2C%20and%20goals%20%E2%80%94%20all%20useful%20suggestions%2C%20to%20be%20fair%20%E2%80%94%20Pawlisch%20said%20that%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20managing%20a%20team%20or%20steering%20a%20company%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshrinking-labor-force-scariest-number-job-market-hiring-unemployment-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emurky%20economic%20waters%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20focusing%20solely%20on%20self-improvement%20won't%20cut%20it.%20Her%20job%20also%20requires%20her%20to%20think%20about%20what%20other%20people%20want%20and%20need%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20her%20employees%2C%20but%20shareholders%2C%20clients%2C%20and%20consumers%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20these%20business%20books%20have%20similar%20ideas%2C%26quot%3B%20Pawlisch%20told%20me.%20Not%20only%20that%2C%20but%20they%20tend%20to%20be%20written%20by%20the%20same%20kind%20of%20person%3A%20white%2C%20college-educated%20men%20from%20stable%20to%20prosperous%20socioeconomic%20backgrounds.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20these%20are%20books%20written%20by%20and%20for%20people%20with%20similar%20access%20to%20resources%2C%20capital%2C%20and%2C%20ultimately%2C%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20can%20be%20very%20limiting%20in%20a%20business%20setting%2C%20especially%20when%20you're%20looking%20at%20who's%20going%20to%20be%20a%20part%20of%20your%20team%2C%20or%20who%20you're%20selling%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20Pawlisch%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20only%20consuming%20the%20media%20that%20mirrors%20your%20own%20identity%2C%20you're%20really%20losing%20the%20ability%20to%20connect%20across%20lines.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20flipside%2C%20when%20Pawlisch%20reads%20a%20novel%20like%20her%20longtime%20favorite%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIsabel%20Allende's%20%26quot%3BThe%20House%20of%20the%20Spirits%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20feels%20like%20she's%20discovering%20something%20new.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFiction%20builds%20the%20muscle%20memory%20for%20nuance%2C%20contradiction%2C%20imagination%2C%26quot%3B%20Pawlisch%20continued.%20%26quot%3BThe%20people%20who%20are%20writing%20fiction%2C%20and%20the%20stories%20they're%20writing%20about%2C%20will%20give%20you%20perspectives%20that%20are%20completely%20outside%20of%20this%20bubble%2C%20this%20echo%20chamber%2C%20that%20we're%20all%20existing%20in%20within%20corporate%20America.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20Pawlisch%20is%20an%20avid%20fiction%20reader%20shouldn't%20come%20as%20a%20shock%3B%20women%20dominate%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2025%2F07%2F03%2Farts%2Fstraight-white-male-novelists.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecurrent%20fiction%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20both%20as%20readers%20and%20authors.%20National%20surveys%20consistently%20show%20that%20women%20are%20more%20likely%20than%20men%20to%20say%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amacad.org%2Fhumanities-indicators%2Fhumanities-american-life-survey%2Fhumanities-american-life-insights-literature%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethey%20read%20fiction%20often%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20more%20likely%20to%20say%20they've%20read%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.arts.gov%2Fimpact%2Fresearch%2Fpublications%2Fus-patterns-arts-participation-full-report-2017-survey-public-participation-arts%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20novel%20or%20short%20story%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20past%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20despite%20making%20up%20over%2050%25%20of%20the%20US%20population%2C%20women%20are%20underrepresented%20in%20the%20highest%20echelons%20of%20the%20corporate%20world%3A%20They%20make%20up%20just%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-girl-boss-women-musk-zuckerberg-dimon-alpha-male-backlash-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E10.4%25%20of%20CEOs%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20Fortune%20500%20companies.%20The%20data%20points%20to%20an%20obvious%20disconnect%3A%20the%20people%20most%20likely%20to%20read%20fiction%20and%20reap%20the%20business-minded%20benefits%20are%20rarely%20the%20ones%20holding%20the%20top%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2268099f6a-ced3-449a-a75b-5b65b527c2f6%5C%22%3EReading%20fiction%20has%20many%20leadership%20benefits%20%E2%80%94%20it%20just%20needs%20a%20rebrand%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20all%20men%20are%20missing%20out.%20When%20I%20began%20asking%20professionals%20to%20share%20insight%20into%20their%20bookshelves%2C%20I%20expected%20to%20hear%20from%20businesswomen%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-goodreads%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoodreads%20accounts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20perhaps%20even%20enthusiastic%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-changes-book-publishing-marketing-author-careers-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBookTok%20scrollers%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20did%20not%20expect%20to%20hear%20from%20over%20a%20dozen%20successful%20men%20across%20industries%20%E2%80%94%20including%20marketing%20executives%2C%20college%20professors%2C%20tech%20entrepreneurs%2C%20and%20one%20employment%20attorney%20%E2%80%94%20who%20told%20me%20that%20reading%20fiction%20has%20sharpened%20their%20ability%20to%20communicate%20in%20meetings%2C%20network%20with%20charm%2C%20deliver%20difficult%20feedback%20without%20discouraging%20staff%2C%20and%20even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquiet-cracking-warning-signs-work-employees-for-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edetect%20slumps%20in%20company%20morale%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMen%20who%20read%20fiction%20are%20simply%20better%20at%20reading%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Jordan%20Geary%2C%20an%20Emmy%20Award-winning%20creative%20producer%20and%20longtime%20TV%20executive%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20leg%20day%20for%20your%20soul.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGeary%2C%20who%20told%20me%20he's%20enjoyed%20reading%20everything%20from%20%26quot%3BThe%20Count%20of%20Monte%20Cristo%26quot%3B%20to%20%26quot%3BThe%20Devil%20Wears%20Prada%2C%26quot%3B%20credits%20fiction%20with%20stretching%20him%20socially%20and%20creatively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMen%2C%20conversationally%2C%20have%20become%20robots%2C%20and%20I%20think%20it's%20because%20they're%20flocking%20to%20this%20nonfiction%20stuff%20that%20reads%20like%20instruction%20manuals%2C%26quot%3B%20Geary%20added.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20like%2C%20'First%20you%20do%20this%2C%20then%20you%20do%20this%2C%20then%20you%20do%20this%2C%20the%20end.'%20There's%20no%20creativity%2C%20there's%20no%20mystery%2C%20there's%20no%20adaptability%20asked%20of%20you%20or%20anybody.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERicardo%20Fayet%2C%20cofounder%20and%20CMO%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Felainepofeldt%2F2016%2F11%2F29%2Fthis-startup-aims-to-take-the-pain-out-of-diy-publishing%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eonline%20publishing%20hub%20Reedsy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20the%20epic%20fantasy%20books%20he%20reads%20for%20fun%20often%20feature%20complex%20leaders%20and%20high-stakes%20situations%20that%20inform%20his%20own%20decision-making%20as%20a%20manager.%20Yet%20in%20both%20his%20personal%20and%20professional%20life%2C%20he's%20found%20these%20types%20of%20books%20are%20trivialized%20as%20vehicles%20for%20escapism%20%E2%80%94%20as%20a%20pastime%20that%20isn't%20%26quot%3Bproductive%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20rather%20than%20a%20useful%20looking-glass%20for%20real-world%20dilemmas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFiction%20is%20always%20presented%20as%20an%20escape%20from%20the%20horrible%20world%20that%20we%20live%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20Fayet%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20talk%20a%20lot%20about%20the%20life%20lessons%20that%20you%20learn%20in%20fiction.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPawlisch%20echoed%20his%20observation.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20this%20notion%20that%20serious%20people%20read%20nonfiction%2C%20while%20fiction%20is%20just%20seen%20as%20indulgent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20that%20novels%20are%20devoid%20of%20important%20themes%20and%20lessons%3B%20it's%20that%20their%20value%20is%20usually%20not%20packaged%20in%20direct%2C%20easy-to-memorize%20ways%20that%20appeal%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-moved-to-italy-new-definition-of-success-better-life-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproductivity-obsessed%20workforce%3C%2Fa%3E.%20What%20these%20books%20need%20is%20a%20reputational%20rebrand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20ask%20a%20fiction%20reader%2C%20'What%20life%20lessons%20did%20you%20learn%20from%20your%20last%20book%3F'%20It's%20a%20hard%20question%20to%20answer%2C%26quot%3B%20Fayet%20explained.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20read%20a%20nonfiction%20book%20%5Babout%5D%20five%20ways%20to%20make%20friends%2C%20then%20you%20have%20a%20recap%20list%20with%20tip%20one%2C%20tip%20two%2C%20tip%20three%2C%20tip%20four%2C%20tip%20five.%20And%20so%20you're%20able%20to%20recite%20that%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20book.%20But%20it%20maybe%20doesn't%20enter%20your%20subconscious%20as%20much%20as%20fiction.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20research%20has%20shown%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fscience%2Fbiology%2Fwant-to-remember-more-make-more-mistakes-2d195a6f%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erote%20memorization%20is%20ineffective%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20superficial%20compared%20to%20more%20interactive%2C%20immersive%20learning%20methods%20that%20promote%20retention%2C%20recall%2C%20and%20critical%20thinking.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Farticles%2FPMC7018408%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2020%20article%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%20the%20British%20Journal%20of%20General%20Practice%20titled%20%26quot%3BReading%20fiction%3A%20the%20benefits%20are%20numerous%26quot%3B%20noted%20that%20people%20%26quot%3Bremember%20facts%20better%20when%20woven%20into%20a%20narrative.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20fiction%20readers%2C%20the%20value%20lies%20not%20in%20isolated%20facts%20but%20in%20the%20relevant%20themes%20and%20moral%20dilemmas%20that%20shed%20light%20on%20the%20human%20experience.%20Geary%2C%20the%20TV%20executive%2C%20told%20me%20that%20re-reading%20Michael%20Crichton's%201990%20novel%20%26quot%3BJurassic%20Park%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20childhood%20favorite%2C%20hit%20differently%20during%20a%20time%20when%20he%20was%20overextended%20at%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20Geary's%20job%20may%20not%20involve%20reanimated%20dinosaurs%2C%20he%20related%20to%20the%20book's%20fictional%20entrepreneurs'%20belief%20that%20they%20could%20manage%20and%20contain%20every%20detail%20of%20their%20theme%20park%2C%20famously%20to%20their%20detriment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20reading%20this%20book%20at%20the%20same%20time%20that%20I'm%20working%20on%20six%20TV%20shows%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20and%20I%20was%20banging%20my%20head%20against%20the%20wall%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20make%20everything%20work%20perfectly%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explained.%20%26quot%3BIt%20made%20me%20just%20say%2C%20'Oh%2C%20there's%20so%20much%20chaos.%20There%20are%20so%20many%20moving%20parts%2C%20I%20can't%20control%20everything.'%20And%20it%20really%20helped%20me%20out.%20It%20just%20lowered%20my%20blood%20pressure%20and%20made%20me%20a%20better%20executive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20believes%20the%20ability%20to%20envision%20a%20different%20reality%2C%20probe%20the%20psyches%20of%20other%20people%2C%20and%20consider%20complex%20solutions%20to%20complex%20problems%20are%20skills%20that%20distinguish%20the%20number%20crunchers%20from%20the%20visionaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGreat%20leaders%20aren't%20data%20dumpers%2C%26quot%3B%20Geary%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20storytellers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceos-business-leaders-books-fiction-not-nonfiction-2025-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22publ