nder%20of%20Children%20First%2C%20states%20a%20starting%20point%3A%20%E2%80%9CNeurotypical%20is%20this%20idea%20of%20normalcy%20that%20one%20can%20diverge%20from%2C%20and%20hence%20be%20neurodivergent%2C%20but%20the%20idea%20of%20normalcy%20itself%20needs%20questioning%2C%20right%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20words%20push%20me%20to%20look%20closer%20at%20the%20idea%20of%20%E2%80%9Cnormal%E2%80%9D%20itself%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20in%20the%20context%20of%20neurodiversity%2C%20but%20in%20how%20we%20parent%2C%20educate%2C%20and%20measure%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20did%20it%20become%20normal%20for%20university%20cut-offs%20to%20be%20in%20the%20nineties%3F%20For%20children%20to%20attend%20class%20after%20class%20to%20%E2%80%9Cupskill%E2%80%9D%3F%20To%20start%20as%20young%20as%20possible%20so%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20miss%20out%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20vividly%20recall%20a%20conversation%20with%20my%20daughter%20years%20ago%20while%20discussing%20extracurricular%20activities.%20She%20told%20me%20matter-of-factly%20to%20enrol%20her%20in%20as%20many%20classes%20as%20possible%2C%20like%20her%20peers.%20%E2%80%9CBecause%20we%20must%20keep%20busy%2C%20no%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20laughed%20it%20off%20then%2C%20but%20later%20returned%20to%20ask%20what%20she%20meant.%20We%20ended%20up%20talking%20about%20how%20we%20assume%20something%20is%20normal%20simply%20because%20everyone%20does%20it.%20%E2%80%9CEveryone%20is%20always%20on%20their%20phones%20these%20days%2C%20but%20that%E2%80%99s%20not%20normal%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20concluded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20struck%20me%20that%20what%20we%20normalise%20often%20has%20little%20to%20do%20with%20actual%20needs%2C%20and%20everything%20to%20do%20with%20patterns%20we%E2%80%99ve%20accepted%20without%20question.%20This%20one-size-fits-all%20idea%20that%20fails%20to%20reflect%20real%20lives%20%E2%80%94%20and%20into%20that%20gap%20fall%20many%20children.%20When%20we%20encounter