r%20to%20her%20husband%2C%20Children%20First%20co-founder%20Dr%20Amit%20Sen%2C%20and%20as%20mother%20to%20a%20son%20with%20ADHD%20%E2%80%94%20helped%20her%20have%20%E2%80%9Can%20easy%20relationship%20with%20the%20diagnosis%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAnita%20is%20blunt%20about%20it.%20%E2%80%9CLabels%20are%20not%20so%20great%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%20%E2%80%9CFor%20us%2C%20they%E2%80%99re%20important%20to%20an%20extent%20because%20we%20work%20with%20children%20and%20some%20broad%20directives%20are%20helpful.%20But%20each%20child%20is%20different%2C%20and%20too%20much%20of%20the%20specifics%20are%20not%20useful.%20In%20the%20day-to-day%20of%20life%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20not%20much%20need%20for%20such%20language.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Swaati%2C%20the%20paperwork%20was%20just%20a%20means%20to%20access%20accommodations.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20reading%20and%20my%20interactions%20with%20the%20right%20kind%20of%20people%20helped%20me%20make%20my%20peace%20with%20how%20autism%20is%20an%20umbrella%20term%2C%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20still%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F358168%2Fpeople-with-nonspeaking-autism-in-india-talking-fingers-book-authors-padma-jyothi-chitra-paul%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esomething%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20fully%20understand%20yet%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20know%20my%20child%20is%20not%20the%20sum%20of%20these%20points.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F417379%2Fmugdha-kalra-shares-parenting-methods-raising-autistic-child-world-autism-awareness-day%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChildren%20are%20meant%20to%20be%20loved%20and%20cared%20for%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20not%20analysed%2C%20right%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPriya%20treats%20the%20assessment%20as%20%E2%80%9Csomething